HEADWORD: icky
<hw>icky</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>very bad; repulsive;
unpleasant; distasteful.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> crappy, lousy, rotten, shitty, stinking,
stinky.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>sticky; <as>as, <ex>icky</ex>, sticky
goo</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gooey.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Overly sentimental; -- of stories or
dramas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

